              <h1>Rune Guardian</h1>
              <div class="statblock">
                <p class="description">A carved rune detaches itself from the wall and floats silently in
                  midair, glowing with arcane energy.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="statblock">
                <p class="title">Rune Guardian <span class="level">CR 1</span></p>
                <p><b>XP 400</b><br> N Tiny <a
                    href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/bestiary/rules-for-monsters/creature-types#TOC-Construct">construct</a><br>
                  <b>Init</b> +6; <b>Senses</b> <a
                    href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/special-abilities#TOC-Darkvision">darkvision</a>
                  60 ft., <a
                    href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/special-abilities#TOC-Low-Light-Vision">low-light
                    vision</a>; <a href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/perception">Perception</a> +3
                </p>
                <p class="divider">DEFENSE</p>
                <p><b>AC</b> 14, <a href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Touch-Attacks">touch</a> 14,
                  <a href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/conditions#TOC-Flat-Footed">flat-footed</a>
                  12 (+2 <a
                    href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Dexterity-Dex-">Dex</a>,
                  +2 <a href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/glossary#TOC-Size-Bonus">size</a>)<br>
                  <b>hp</b> 11 (2d10); <a
                    href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/bestiary/rules-for-monsters/universal-monster-rules/#Fast_Healing_Ex">fast
                    healing</a> 1<br> <b>Fort</b> +0, <b>Ref</b> +2, <b>Will</b> +2<br> <b>Immune</b> <a
                    href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/bestiary/rules-for-monsters/universal-monster-rules#TOC-Construct-Traits-Ex-">construct
                    traits</a>; <b>SR</b> 12<br> <b>Weaknesses</b> school vulnerability
                </p>
                <p class="divider">OFFENSE</p>

                <p><b>Speed</b> fly 60 ft. (perfect)<br> <b>Melee</b> slam +2 (1d2–2)<br> <b>Special
                    Attacks</b> sin magic<br> <b>Spell-Like Abilities</b> (CL 3rd; <a
                    href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic#TOC-Concentration">concentration</a> +4)</p>
                <p style="margin-left:40px"> <b>At will</b>—<a class="spell"
                    href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic/all-spells/b/burning-hands">burning hands</a> (DC
                  12), <a class="spell" href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic/all-spells/c/color-spray">color
                    spray</a> (DC 12), <a class="spell"
                    href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic/all-spells/h/hold-portal">hold
                    portal</a>, <a class="spell"
                    href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic/all-spells/r/ray-of-enfeeblement">ray
                    of enfeeblement</a> (DC 12), <a class="spell"
                    href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic/all-spells/r/reduce-person">reduce person</a> (DC
                  12), <a class="spell" href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic/all-spells/s/sleep">sleep</a> (DC
                  12), <a class="spell" href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic/all-spells/s/summon-monster">summon monster
                    I</a>
                </p>
                <p class="divider">STATISTICS</p>
                <p><b>Str</b> 6, <b>Dex</b> 15, <b>Con</b> —, <b>Int</b> 11, <b>Wis</b> 14, <b>Cha</b> 12<br>
                  <b>Base Atk</b> +2; <b>CMB</b> +2; <b>CMD</b> 10 (can’t be <a
                    href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Trip">tripped</a>)<br>
                  <b>Feats</b> <a href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/feats/combat-feats/improved-initiative-combat">Improved
                    Initiative</a><br> <b>Skills</b> <a href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/fly">Fly</a>
                  +18, <a href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/perception">Perception</a> +3, <a
                    href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/stealth">Stealth</a> +12<br> <b>Languages</b> does
                  not speak
                </p>
                <p class="divider">SPECIAL ABILITIES</p>
                <h4>School Vulnerability (Ex)</h4>
                <p>A rune guardian’s <a
                    href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/special-abilities#TOC-Spell-Resistance">spell
                    resistance</a> does not apply against spells or effects from its opposition schools. Rune
                  guardians of envy are vulnerable to <a
                    href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic#TOC-Evocation">evocation</a> and
                  <a href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic#TOC-Necromancy">necromancy</a> spells, rune guardians
                  of gluttony are vulnerable to <a href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic#TOC-Abjuration">abjuration</a>
                  and <a href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic#TOC-Enchantment">enchantment</a> spells, rune
                  guardians of greed are vulnerable to <a
                    href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic#TOC-Enchantment">enchantment</a>
                  and <a href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic#TOC-Illusion">illusion</a> spells, rune guardians of
                  lust are vulnerable to <a href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic#TOC-Necromancy">necromancy</a> and <a
                    href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic#TOC-Transmutation">transmutation</a> spells, rune
                  guardians of pride are vulnerable to <a
                    href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic#TOC-Conjuration">conjuration</a>
                  and <a href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic#TOC-Transmutation">transmutation</a> spells, rune
                  guardians of sloth are vulnerable to <a
                    href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic#TOC-Evocation">evocation</a>
                  and
                  <a href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic#TOC-Illusion">illusion</a> spells, and rune guardians
                  of wrath are vulnerable to <a href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic#TOC-Abjuration">abjuration</a> and
                  <a href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic#TOC-Conjuration">conjuration</a> spells.
                </p>
                <h4>Sin Magic (Sp)</h4>
                <p>A rune guardian has a single <a
                    href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic#TOC-Spell-Like-Abilities-Sp-">spell-like
                    ability</a>,
                  usable at will, from the school of magic associated with the reward of rule it represents.
                  Rune guardians of envy cast <a class="spell"
                    href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic/all-spells/h/hold-portal">hold portal</a>, rune
                  guardians of gluttony cast <a class="spell"
                    href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic/all-spells/r/ray-of-enfeeblement">ray of
                    enfeeblement</a>, rune guardians of greed cast <a class="spell"
                    href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic/all-spells/r/reduce-person">reduce person</a>, rune
                  guardians of lust cast <a class="spell"
                    href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic/all-spells/s/sleep">sleep</a>,
                  rune guardians of
                  pride cast <a class="spell" href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic/all-spells/c/color-spray">color
                    spray</a>,
                  rune
                  guardians of sloth cast <a class="spell"
                    href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic/all-spells/s/summon-monster">summon monster I</a>,
                  and rune guardians of wrath cast <a class="spell"
                    href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic/all-spells/b/burning-hands">burning hands</a>.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="statblock">
                <p class="divider">ECOLOGY</p>
                <p><b>Environment</b> any<br> <b>Organization</b> solitary, pair, or syllabary (7 rune
                  guardians, 1 of each sin)<br> <b>Treasure</b> none</p>
                <p>Rune guardians are animated <a
                    href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/bestiary/rules-for-monsters/creature-types#TOC-Construct">constructs</a>
                  created to guard laboratories, ossuaries, and repositories of lore. Each rune guardian is
                  dedicated to one of the seven rewards of rule (now known as the seven sins of the soul), and
                  empowered with that sin’s associated school of magic. As such, there are seven varieties of
                  rune guardian, each recognizable by its shape—that of the rune representing that specific sin
                  and arcane school. Unlike <a
                    href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/bestiary/monster-listings/constructs/golem">golems</a>, rune
                  guardians are intelligent, able to follow complex orders and pursue intruders. They were built
                  to coordinate with other servants of the rune lords—for example, an envy guardian’s <a class="spell"
                    href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic/all-spells/h/hold-portal">hold portal</a>
                  ability is more dangerous when used to lock someone in a room with a servitor monster.</p>
                <p>A rune guardian is approximately 1 foot in diameter and weighs around 10 pounds.</p>
                <h3>Variants</h3>
                <p>The statistics presented here represent only the least specimen created by the ancient
                  runelords, with the power of a single 1st-level spell. Other variants exist, with different <a
                    href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic#TOC-Spell-Like-Abilities-Sp-">spell-like abilities</a>
                  or ones of increasing magical power.</p>
                <p>Rune guardians are always tied to one school of magic, and all of a rune guardian’s <a
                    href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/glossary#TOC-Spell-Like-Abilities-Sp-">spell-like</a>
                  abilities must come from that school. For example, a rune guardian of wrath might cast <a
                    class="spell" href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic/all-spells/m/magic-missile">magic
                    missile</a> or <a class="spell"
                    href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic/all-spells/s/shocking-grasp">shocking
                    grasp</a> instead
                  of <a class="spell" href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic/all-spells/b/burning-hands">burning
                    hands</a>. In addition to the <a
                    href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic#TOC-Spell-Like-Abilities-Sp-">spell-like
                    ability</a>
                  listed above, more powerful rune guardians of gluttony might possess the ability to cast <a
                    class="spell"
                    href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic/all-spells/b/blindness-deafness"><i>blindness/deafness</i></a>
                  or <a class="spell" href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic/all-spells/r/ray-of-exhaustion">ray
                    of exhaustion</a>.</p>
                <h3>Construction</h3>
                <p>A rune guardian’s body is carved from a single block of semiprecious stone, then polished and
                  treated with rare dusts and oils worth at least 500 gp.</p>
                <p><b>CL</b> 11th; <b>Price</b> 6,500 gp</p>
                <p class="divider">CONSTRUCTION REQUIREMENTS</p>
                <p><b>Feats</b> <a
                    href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/feats/item-creation-feats/craft-construct-item-creation">Craft
                    Construct</a>, <a class="spell" href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic/all-spells/f/fly">fly</a>, <a
                    class="spell" href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic/all-spells/g/geas-quest"><i>geas/quest</i></a>,
                  plus <a class="spell" href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic/all-spells/b/burning-hands">burning
                    hands</a>, <a class="spell" href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic/all-spells/c/color-spray">color
                    spray</a>,
                  <a class="spell" href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic/all-spells/h/hold-portal">hold
                    portal</a>, <a class="spell"
                    href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic/all-spells/r/ray-of-enfeeblement">ray of
                    enfeeblement</a>, <a class="spell"
                    href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic/all-spells/r/reduce-person">reduce
                    person</a>, <a class="spell" href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic/all-spells/s/sleep">sleep</a>, or
                  <a class="spell" href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic/all-spells/s/summon-monster">summon
                    monster I</a>; <b>Special</b> creator must be <a
                    href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic#TOC-Caster-Level">caster
                    level</a> 11th; <b>Skill</b>
                  <a href="https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/craft">Craft</a> (stonecarving) DC 16; <b>Cost</b>
                  3,500 gp
                </p>
